nodes.text: The Arbiter was a name which Yrica Quell, a New Republic pilot who was working as a mole in the Galactic Empire's 204th Imperial Fighter Wing, conjured when trying to remember the name of the Imperial Colonel Madrighast's Imperial-class Star Destroyer, the Unyielding, in 5 ABY.
The Arbiter was mentioned in the 2021 novel Victory's Price, the third and final installment of the Star Wars: Alphabet Squadron trilogy which was written by Alexander Freed.
